@@ -0,0 +1,14 @@
+# DispatchInputEventResult Object
+
+* `inputEventId` string - Unique identifier assigned to this dispatch request.
+* `consumed` boolean - Whether Chromium reported that the input event was
+  consumed. For keyboard events this is the value callers should use to decide
+  whether a follow-up text insertion should be skipped.
+* `ackState` string - Raw Chromium input ACK state for diagnostics and advanced
+  routing decisions. Can be `consumed`, `not-consumed`, `no-consumer-exists`,
+  `ignored`, `set-non-blocking`, `set-non-blocking-due-to-fling`, or `unknown`.
+* `ackSource` string - Thread or component that produced the Chromium input ACK.
+  Can be `main-thread`, `compositor-thread`, `browser`, or `unknown`.
+* `frame` [WebFrameMain](../web-frame-main.md) (optional) - Frame that received
+  the input event, when Electron can map the target renderer widget back to a
+  frame.
