diff --git a/docs/api/structures/dispatch-input-key-event-params.md b/docs/api/structures/dispatch-input-key-event-params.md
new file mode 100644
index 0000000000..d3719f8d05
--- /dev/null
+++ b/docs/api/structures/dispatch-input-key-event-params.md
@@ -0,0 +1,26 @@
+# DispatchInputKeyEventParams Object
+
+* `kind` string - Can be `key`.
+* `type` string - Keyboard event phase to dispatch. Can be `rawKeyDown`,
+  `keyDown`, `keyUp`, or `char`.
+* `modifiers` Integer (optional) - Bit field of active modifiers using the
+  Chrome DevTools Protocol layout: Alt=1, Ctrl=2, Meta=4, Shift=8.
+* `timestamp` number (optional) - Event timestamp in seconds since the Unix
+  epoch. The current event time is used when omitted.
+* `text` string (optional) - Text generated by the key event, if any.
+* `unmodifiedText` string (optional) - Text generated by the key event without
+  modifier effects, if any.
+* `code` string (optional) - DOM `KeyboardEvent.code` value, for example `KeyA`
+  or `Enter`.
+* `key` string (optional) - DOM `KeyboardEvent.key` value, for example `a` or
+  `Enter`.
+* `windowsVirtualKeyCode` Integer (optional) - Windows virtual key code. When
+  omitted, Electron derives a best-effort value from `code` and `key`.
+* `nativeVirtualKeyCode` Integer (optional) - Native virtual key code. When
+  omitted, Electron uses the resolved Windows virtual key code.
+* `autoRepeat` boolean (optional) - Whether this key event is an auto-repeat
+  event.
+* `isKeypad` boolean (optional) - Whether this key event originated from the
+  numeric keypad.
+* `isSystemKey` boolean (optional) - Whether this is a system key event.
+* `location` Integer (optional) - DOM `KeyboardEvent.location` value.
diff --git a/docs/api/structures/dispatch-input-mouse-event-params.md b/docs/api/structures/dispatch-input-mouse-event-params.md
new file mode 100644
index 0000000000..2c5ce8069a
--- /dev/null
+++ b/docs/api/structures/dispatch-input-mouse-event-params.md
@@ -0,0 +1,36 @@
+# DispatchInputMouseEventParams Object
+
+* `kind` string - Can be `mouse`.
+* `type` string - Mouse event phase to dispatch. Can be `mousePressed`,
+  `mouseReleased`, `mouseMoved`, or `mouseWheel`.
+* `x` number - X coordinate relative to the WebContents viewport in CSS pixels.
+* `y` number - Y coordinate relative to the WebContents viewport in CSS pixels.
+* `modifiers` Integer (optional) - Bit field of active modifiers using the
+  Chrome DevTools Protocol layout: Alt=1, Ctrl=2, Meta=4, Shift=8.
+* `timestamp` number (optional) - Event timestamp in seconds since the Unix
+  epoch. The current event time is used when omitted.
+* `button` string (optional) - Mouse button associated with this event. Can be
+  `none`, `left`, `middle`, `right`, `back`, or `forward`.
+* `buttons` Integer (optional) - Bit field of currently pressed mouse buttons:
+  Left=1, Right=2, Middle=4, Back=8, Forward=16.
+* `clickCount` Integer (optional) - Number of consecutive clicks represented by
+  this event.
+* `force` number (optional) - Pointer force in the range [0, 1].
+* `tangentialPressure` number (optional) - Tangential pointer pressure in the
+  range [-1, 1].
+* `tiltX` number (optional) - Pointer tilt on the X axis in degrees, in the
+  range [-90, 90].
+* `tiltY` number (optional) - Pointer tilt on the Y axis in degrees, in the
+  range [-90, 90].
+* `twist` Integer (optional) - Pointer twist in degrees, in the range [0, 359].
+* `deltaX` number (optional) - Horizontal wheel delta. Required when `type` is
+  `mouseWheel`.
+* `deltaY` number (optional) - Vertical wheel delta. Required when `type` is
+  `mouseWheel`.
+* `pointerType` string (optional) - Pointer device type used for the mouse event.
+  Can be `mouse` or `pen`.
+
+`mousePressed`, `mouseMoved`, and `mouseReleased` can be used as one trusted
+mouse sequence. If the page starts a renderer drag from that sequence, Chromium
+will finish the drag source when the release is dispatched, even when the drop
+target is in another frame.
