--- /dev/null
+++ b/docs/api/structures/dispatch-input-touch-point.md
@@ -0,0 +1,17 @@
+# DispatchInputTouchPoint Object
+
+* `id` Integer (optional) - Stable touch point identifier. Either every touch
+  point in the request must provide an id, or none of them should.
+* `x` number - X coordinate relative to the WebContents viewport in CSS pixels.
+* `y` number - Y coordinate relative to the WebContents viewport in CSS pixels.
+* `radiusX` number (optional) - Horizontal radius of the touch contact area.
+* `radiusY` number (optional) - Vertical radius of the touch contact area.
+* `rotationAngle` number (optional) - Rotation angle of the touch contact area.
+* `force` number (optional) - Touch force in the range [0, 1].
+* `tangentialPressure` number (optional) - Tangential pointer pressure in the
+  range [-1, 1].
+* `tiltX` number (optional) - Pointer tilt on the X axis in degrees, in the
+  range [-90, 90].
+* `tiltY` number (optional) - Pointer tilt on the Y axis in degrees, in the
+  range [-90, 90].
+* `twist` Integer (optional) - Pointer twist in degrees, in the range [0, 359].
diff --git a/docs/api/web-contents.md b/docs/api/web-contents.md
index c938475bcd..3ea4901d9a 100644
--- a/docs/api/web-contents.md
+++ b/docs/api/web-contents.md
@@ -2226,6 +2226,25 @@ Sends an input `event` to the page.
 > The [`BrowserWindow`](browser-window.md) containing the contents needs to be focused for
 `sendInputEvent()` to work.
 
+#### `contents.dispatchInputEvent(inputEvent)`
+
+* `inputEvent` [DispatchInputKeyEventParams](structures/dispatch-input-key-event-params.md) | [DispatchInputMouseEventParams](structures/dispatch-input-mouse-event-params.md) | [DispatchInputTouchEventParams](structures/dispatch-input-touch-event-params.md) | [DispatchInputInsertTextEventParams](structures/dispatch-input-insert-text-event-params.md) | [DispatchInputImeSetCompositionEventParams](structures/dispatch-input-ime-set-composition-event-params.md)
+
+Returns `Promise<DispatchInputEventResult>` - resolves with Chromium input ACK
+details for the dispatched event. See
+[DispatchInputEventResult](structures/dispatch-input-event-result.md).
+
+Dispatches an input event to the page. Mouse and touch events are routed by
+coordinate hit testing, so they can target out-of-process child frames. Keyboard,
+text, and IME composition requests are routed to the currently focused frame.
+Mouse dispatches use Chromium's trusted input path and keep renderer-started
+drag sequences in sync, including drops that finish in a different frame from
+the drag source.
+
+The returned `consumed` value is based on Chromium's input ACK state. For
+keyboard events, this is the value callers should use to decide whether a
+follow-up text insertion should be skipped.
+
 #### `contents.beginFrameSubscription([onlyDirty ,]callback)`
 
 * `onlyDirty` boolean (optional) - Defaults to `false`.
